comment._content:
CWGC has this:

THOMPSON, C F W

Rank: Rifleman
Service No: C/12162
Date of Death: 17/09/1916
Age: 21
Regiment/Service: King's Royal Rifle Corps 21st Bn.
Grave Reference XXI. E. 5.
Cemetery CATERPILLAR VALLEY CEMETERY, LONGUEVAL
Additional Information:
Son of George and Rose Ada Thompson, of Long St., Easingwold, York.

comment.author: 69662531@N05
comment._content:
The 1911 census has this:

Charles F W Thompson, aged 16, born Easingwold, Yorkshire, student, lived with his parents - George Thompson, aged 58, born Stillington, Yorkshire, district road surveyor and Rose Ada, aged 55, born Coxwold, Yorkshire, brother - John George, aged 26, born Easingwold, railway clerk and Reginald E Batty, aged 30, born Coxwold, cow keeper (described as the step-son of George)

comment.author: 38811045@N04
comment._content: Original member of the 21st (Service) Battalion, KRRC (Yeoman Rifles) who enlisted Oct/Nov 1915.
